00:49:16,706 --> 00:49:18,435
- Surprise surprise.
- (both giggle)

758
00:49:18,475 --> 00:49:21,535
Right, how's this for ugly?
(roars)

759
00:49:25,815 --> 00:49:28,283
Second place
goes to Lily Enslin.

760
00:49:28,318 --> 00:49:31,446
- (roars)
- That was good.

761
00:49:31,488 --> 00:49:35,049
That's kind of like Beowulf
meets a redneck.

762
00:49:35,091 --> 00:49:39,289
- I like it.
- And first place goes to Katie Enslin.

763
00:49:41,565 --> 00:49:43,590
That is a terror.
That is...

764
00:49:43,633 --> 00:49:45,828
oh, God! Don't show
me that face!

765
00:49:45,869 --> 00:49:47,530
Oh, I can't look
at it again.

766
00:49:49,072 --> 00:49:51,165
Lily:
Whatever you do, don't turn around.

767
00:49:51,208 --> 00:49:52,971
Whatever you do,
don't show us that face.

768
00:50:08,258 --> 00:50:10,351
(static crackling)

769
00:50:28,645 --> 00:50:30,044
(woman crying)

770
00:50:45,595 --> 00:50:47,358
(woman screaming)

771
00:50:47,397 --> 00:50:50,230
(baby crying)

772
00:51:01,411 --> 00:51:03,402
(light tapping)

773
00:51:03,446 --> 00:51:05,880
Ma'am, can you hear me?

774
00:51:09,085 --> 00:51:10,985
Ma'am, I need your help.

775
00:51:12,155 --> 00:51:13,952
Please, ma'am,
can you hear me?

776
00:51:13,990 --> 00:51:16,220
(baby continues crying)

777
00:51:16,259 --> 00:51:19,057
- Kid, be quiet.
- (baby wailing)

778
00:51:19,095 --> 00:51:20,995
Please, ma'am.

779
00:51:21,031 --> 00:51:22,931
(crying intensifying,
echoing)

780
00:51:22,966 --> 00:51:25,662
Quiet!
(groans)

781
00:51:38,715 --> 00:51:38,848
(crying stops)

782
00:51:38,848 --> 00:51:40,440
(crying stops)

783
00:51:40,483 --> 00:51:42,917
(groaning)

784
00:51:48,525 --> 00:51:50,789
(siren blaring
in distance)

785
00:51:55,498 --> 00:51:57,466
(man crying)

786
00:52:18,788 --> 00:52:21,586
Man:
I... wish...

787
00:52:22,592 --> 00:52:25,356
I was dead.

788
00:52:28,631 --> 00:52:30,724
Where's my garden?

789
00:52:32,335 --> 00:52:35,065
I can't smell anything.

790
00:52:35,105 --> 00:52:38,097
I hate this place.

791
00:52:43,246 --> 00:52:45,237
How did I get here?

792
00:52:49,319 --> 00:52:51,184
Pop.

793
00:52:51,221 --> 00:52:52,882
Dad.

794
00:52:54,190 --> 00:52:55,919
It's Michael.

795
00:53:08,104 --> 00:53:10,538
As you are...

796
00:53:10,573 --> 00:53:13,201
I was.

797
00:53:15,879 --> 00:53:17,972
As I am...

798
00:53:21,251 --> 00:53:23,913
you will be.

799
00:53:27,757 --> 00:53:31,215
(woman laughing)

800
00:53:31,261 --> 00:53:33,092
(panting)

801
00:53:45,275 --> 00:53:47,300
Mike's voice:
Maybe I'm not real.

802
00:53:49,746 --> 00:53:51,839
Maybe I'm just
having a nightmare...

803
00:53:54,384 --> 00:53:56,648
an incredibly vivid

804
00:53:56,686 --> 00:53:59,120
lucid nightmare.

805
00:54:01,658 --> 00:54:04,218
When is the last time
I remember going to bed?

806
00:54:04,260 --> 00:54:06,524
(ticking)

807
00:54:06,563 --> 00:54:08,497
I flew in yesterday.

808
00:54:09,632 --> 00:54:12,931
Or was that... today?

809
00:54:13,937 --> 00:54:15,905
I can't remember.

810
00:54:15,939 --> 00:54:17,930
Was I on a train?

811
00:54:21,478 --> 00:54:23,173
I woke up somewhere

812
00:54:23,213 --> 00:54:25,272
and I had breakfast.

813
00:54:25,315 --> 00:54:28,148
Where was I?
What did I eat?

814
00:54:32,455 --> 00:54:34,446
(rumbling)

815
00:54:36,125 --> 00:54:37,615
Here it comes.

816
00:55:00,450 --> 00:55:03,613
They say you can't die
in your dreams.

817
00:55:03,653 --> 00:55:05,177
Is that true?

818
00:55:14,397 --> 00:55:16,331
(rumbles)

819
00:55:22,405 --> 00:55:24,600
(horns blaring)

820
00:55:24,641 --> 00:55:28,133
The shock
would wake you up.

821
00:55:28,177 --> 00:55:30,111
(horn blaring)

822
00:55:32,715 --> 00:55:35,741
So you couldn't
really die.

823
00:55:40,323 --> 00:55:42,188
All right,
what are our options?

824
00:55:42,225 --> 00:55:45,683
Got the hallway,
got guest rooms on either side,

825
00:55:45,728 --> 00:55:48,822
stairwell,
fire exits.

826
00:55:48,865 --> 00:55:50,628
And that's
the next window...

827
00:55:52,068 --> 00:55:53,558
the next room.

828
00:55:55,038 --> 00:55:58,496
How many feet across
is that?

829
00:55:58,541 --> 00:56:00,202
One...

830
00:56:00,243 --> 00:56:02,108
(rumbles)

831
00:56:02,145 --> 00:56:03,737
...three,

832
00:56:03,780 --> 00:56:05,304
four, five,

833
00:56:05,348 --> 00:56:09,375
six, seven, eight...

834
00:56:09,419 --> 00:56:10,750
nine.

835
00:56:11,754 --> 00:56:14,655
Nine, nine...
18 feet across.

836
00:56:17,427 --> 00:56:20,555
Okay.
I can do this.

837
00:56:26,169 --> 00:56:29,070
If something should happen,
if I should slip and fall,

838
00:56:29,105 --> 00:56:32,268
I want it to be known
that it was an accident.

839
00:56:33,443 --> 00:56:35,377
The room...

840
00:56:35,411 --> 00:56:37,276
did not win.

841
00:56:38,815 --> 00:56:40,442
Okay.

842
00:56:40,483 --> 00:56:42,348
Okay, I can do this.

843
00:56:44,120 --> 00:56:45,519
18 little steps.

844
00:56:53,496 --> 00:56:55,464
Four...

845
00:56:55,498 --> 00:56:57,898
Don't look down.
Five...

846
00:56:59,168 --> 00:57:01,068
Keep moving.

847
00:57:05,475 --> 00:57:07,340
Here we go.

848
00:57:13,016 --> 00:57:15,712
All right.
Okay.

849
00:57:15,752 --> 00:57:17,413
Number nine...

850
00:57:17,453 --> 00:57:18,977
eight...

851
00:57:20,857 --> 00:57:22,222
six...

852
00:57:26,129 --> 00:57:28,597
Where is it?
Where is it?

853
00:57:31,868 --> 00:57:35,167
(horns blaring)

854
00:57:38,007 --> 00:57:39,998
(gasping)

855
00:58:08,004 --> 00:58:09,494
(screams)

856
00:58:09,539 --> 00:58:11,871
(grunting)

857
00:58:18,247 --> 00:58:20,977
(sobbing)

858
00:58:27,090 --> 00:58:28,819
(screams)

859
00:58:49,445 --> 00:58:53,040
(groaning)

860
00:59:26,549 --> 00:59:28,176
(electricity buzzing)

861
00:59:33,790 --> 00:59:35,815
(man screaming)

862
01:00:02,752 --> 01:00:05,482
(static)

863
01:00:05,521 --> 01:00:06,988
Get ahold of yourself.

864
01:00:07,023 --> 01:00:09,116
You're running to places
that aren't real.

865
01:00:11,260 --> 01:00:12,921
(rewinding)

866
01:00:12,962 --> 01:00:15,123
Hotel rooms are naturally
creepy places.

867
01:00:19,268 --> 01:00:22,066
Strangely, the bedroom
has no window.

868
01:00:22,104 --> 01:00:23,696
(groans)

869
01:00:23,739 --> 01:00:26,333
(distorted)
Strangely, the bedroom has no window...

870
01:00:26,375 --> 01:00:29,276
- (footsteps)
- (door slams)

871
01:00:29,312 --> 01:00:31,678
Woman:
Dr. Edwards to Oncology.

872
01:00:34,317 --> 01:00:37,184
Lily:
Please, please.

873
01:00:37,220 --> 01:00:39,051
(sobbing)

874
01:00:43,793 --> 01:00:47,024
No. No. Doctors don't
know everything.

875
01:00:47,063 --> 01:00:49,031
We can get another opinion,
look for other treatment.

876
01:00:49,065 --> 01:00:51,431
- You hear about...
- Look at me.

877
01:00:51,467 --> 01:00:52,991
...miracle cures.
- Lily.

878
01:00:53,035 --> 01:00:56,300
Oh God.
Please, something.

879
01:00:56,339 --> 01:00:59,968
Mike: What kind of god would
do this to a little girl?

880
01:01:00,009 --> 01:01:02,944
(Lily sobbing)

881
01:01:07,817 --> 01:01:10,115
Katie.

882
01:01:10,152 --> 01:01:14,316
Katie:
Daddy, I can't see you.

883
01:01:14,357 --> 01:01:17,520
Daddy, I can't find you.

884
01:01:17,560 --> 01:01:20,028
Daddy, I'm scared.

885
01:01:20,062 --> 01:01:22,587
- Katie.
- I'm scared, Daddy.

886
01:01:22,632 --> 01:01:24,691
Help.

887
01:01:24,734 --> 01:01:26,463
Help me.

888
01:01:26,502 --> 01:01:28,367
Daddy, help me.

889
01:02:05,474 --> 01:02:07,339
Okay, how about
the wireless?

890
01:02:07,376 --> 01:02:08,866
Come on.

891
01:02:16,218 --> 01:02:18,550
Give me a signal.
Give me a signal.

892
01:02:18,587 --> 01:02:20,919
- (beeps)
- Computer: Good evening, Mike.

893
01:02:22,024 --> 01:02:23,491
Oh, yes!

894
01:02:24,860 --> 01:02:28,626
- (beeps)
- Mike?

895
01:02:29,632 --> 01:02:31,293
Mike, is that...
is that you?

896
01:02:31,334 --> 01:02:33,063
- I can barely see you.
- Yes yes.

897
01:02:33,102 --> 01:02:36,538
- It's like seeing a ghost.
- No no no. Yes, it's me.

898
01:02:36,572 --> 01:02:38,403
- It's me. It's Mike.
- This is a little bizarre.

899
01:02:38,441 --> 01:02:40,568
I mean, I haven't talked
to you in a year

900
01:02:40,609 --> 01:02:42,668
and suddenly you pop up
in a box on my computer.

901
01:02:42,712 --> 01:02:45,044
I'm sorry, Lily.
Listen to me, please, quickly.

902
01:02:45,081 --> 01:02:47,675
Look, I'm at work, okay? So why don't
you call me at home tonight?

903
01:02:47,717 --> 01:02:51,209
I'm trapped in this room,
this place.

904
01:02:51,253 --> 01:02:53,448
Mike, you're always trapped in weird
places. That's your job.

905
01:02:53,489 --> 01:02:55,354
- No no, please, Lily. Listen to me.
- (phone rings)

906
01:02:55,391 --> 01:02:57,222
- Please.
- Lily Enslin.

907
01:02:57,259 --> 01:02:59,227
- Hi. Yeah yeah.
- Lily!

908
01:02:59,261 --> 01:03:01,320
- I've got those. I'll be right down.
- No. Lily!

909
01:03:01,364 --> 01:03:03,662
Lily, please!
Call the cops.

910
01:03:03,699 --> 01:03:06,099
Send them
to the Dolphin Hotel.

911
01:03:06,135 --> 01:03:07,864
I'll call you back.

912
01:03:10,439 --> 01:03:12,634
- You're in the city?
- Yes!

913
01:03:12,675 --> 01:03:15,166
- 2254 Lexington.
- What are you doing in New York?

914
01:03:15,211 --> 01:03:18,647
I'll tell you later.
The Dolphin Hotel, room 1408.

915
01:03:18,681 --> 01:03:20,649
- That's just perfect.
- Please.

916
01:03:20,683 --> 01:03:22,514
You walk out, you disappear.
Leaving me what?

917
01:03:22,551 --> 01:03:24,815
Not divorced. Separated?
I don't know, it's not clear.

918
01:03:24,854 --> 01:03:27,584
- Suddenly you need me?
- Lily, I'm in a real bad spot here.

919
01:03:27,623 --> 01:03:30,387
- I'm in danger. You understand?
- Okay, Mike. Slow down.

920
01:03:30,426 --> 01:03:31,654
You're not making
any sense.

921
01:03:31,694 --> 01:03:34,822
There's something trying
to kill me right now.

922
01:03:38,734 --> 01:03:40,497
No, Lily!

923
01:03:40,536 --> 01:03:42,663
No no no!

924
01:04:06,929 --> 01:04:08,760
(water pattering)

925
01:04:43,666 --> 01:04:45,429
I've got a knife!

926
01:04:50,473 --> 01:04:51,701
(grunting)

927
01:05:01,050 --> 01:05:03,041
(mumbling)
That's the way out.

928
01:05:03,085 --> 01:05:05,144
Or that way.
Or that way.

929
01:05:08,157 --> 01:05:09,351
All right,
that's the way out.

930
01:05:09,391 --> 01:05:10,858
(baby crying)

931
01:05:10,893 --> 01:05:12,986
Lady, let me in!

932
01:05:13,028 --> 01:05:16,759
- Help! Help!
- Please, sleep.

933
01:05:16,799 --> 01:05:19,529
- Lady, I'm coming through!
- Mike!

934
01:05:19,568 --> 01:05:22,731
Mike, can you help me?
Where'd you go?

935
01:05:22,771 --> 01:05:26,207
Mike: I got to get some cigarettes.
You want something?

936
01:05:27,943 --> 01:05:30,309
Jesus Christ!

937
01:05:32,414 --> 01:05:34,143
Mike:
I've got to go. I'll be in California.

938
01:05:34,183 --> 01:05:36,117
Mike, you can't do this.

939
01:05:36,152 --> 01:05:38,382
She needs you.
She lost a kid too.

940
01:05:38,420 --> 01:05:40,888
You've got an amazing talent
for stating the obvious, Pop.

941
01:05:40,923 --> 01:05:42,151
You think
I don't know that?

942
01:05:42,191 --> 01:05:44,182
I'm trying to talk
some sense into your head!

943
01:05:44,226 --> 01:05:46,990
- Don't put your hands on me, old man!
- Mike!

944
01:05:47,029 --> 01:05:50,157
Talk? Why change what appears to be
the habit of a lifetime, Pop?

945
01:05:50,199 --> 01:05:51,632
You were always great
at passing judgment,

946
01:05:51,667 --> 01:05:53,567
but the problem is
you never gave a shit.

947
01:05:53,602 --> 01:05:56,537
I never gave a shit
because you're a bullshit writer!

948
01:06:01,110 --> 01:06:02,441
Shit!

949
01:06:10,619 --> 01:06:12,143
Hello!

950
01:06:17,459 --> 01:06:18,619
Oh.

951
01:06:43,652 --> 01:06:45,017
Kevin O'Malley.

952
01:06:50,492 --> 01:06:53,154
(screams)

953
01:06:55,798 --> 01:06:57,425
No.

954
01:06:57,466 --> 01:06:59,434
No no no no no no.

955
01:07:00,536 --> 01:07:03,061
I can't help you.

956
01:07:03,105 --> 01:07:04,538
I can't help you.

957
01:07:06,041 --> 01:07:08,601
No!

958
01:08:00,229 --> 01:08:02,220
(groans)

959
01:08:04,767 --> 01:08:06,860
It's good to be back.

960
01:08:11,674 --> 01:08:13,369
That's enough of that.

961
01:08:22,351 --> 01:08:24,148
Alcohol.

962
01:08:26,188 --> 01:08:28,247
I was just checking to see
if the accommodations

963
01:08:28,290 --> 01:08:29,882
are exceeding
your expectations.

964
01:08:29,925 --> 01:08:32,120
You know goddamn well
they are!

965
01:08:32,161 --> 01:08:35,028
- What do you want from me?
- No no no.

966
01:08:35,064 --> 01:08:37,396
What do you want?

967
01:08:37,433 --> 01:08:40,129
What do you want,
Mr. Enslin?

968
01:08:40,169 --> 01:08:42,831
- You sought this room.
- It was a job. I was doing the job.

969
01:08:42,871 --> 01:08:44,896
- I beg your pardon?
- My job! I'm a writer.

970
01:08:44,940 --> 01:08:47,909
Oh, that's right.
You don't believe in anything.

971
01:08:47,943 --> 01:08:49,638
You like shattering
people's hopes.

972
01:08:49,678 --> 01:08:50,975
Oh, that's bullshit!

973
01:08:51,013 --> 01:08:52,776
Why do you think people
believe in ghosts?

974
01:08:52,815 --> 01:08:55,181
For fun?
No.

975
01:08:55,217 --> 01:08:58,653
It's the prospect
of something after death.

976
01:08:58,687 --> 01:09:01,918
How many spirits
have you broken?

977
01:09:01,957 --> 01:09:03,754
Mike's voice:
She was in so much pain.

978
01:09:03,792 --> 01:09:05,851
Lily: I'm sure she's smiling down
on us right now.

979
01:09:05,894 --> 01:09:08,863
What do you want
from me?

980
01:09:08,897 --> 01:09:10,194
Huh?

981
01:09:10,232 --> 01:09:13,258
What do you want
from me?

982
01:09:13,302 --> 01:09:14,963
You...

983
01:09:15,971 --> 01:09:17,268
you little...

984
01:09:17,306 --> 01:09:20,275
(muttering)

985
01:09:20,309 --> 01:09:22,869
(yelling)
What do you want?

986
01:09:22,911 --> 01:09:24,902
What?!

987
01:09:27,950 --> 01:09:31,750
I want my drink!

988
01:09:43,432 --> 01:09:46,162
You win.
You win.

989
01:09:53,842 --> 01:09:55,639
- Katie: Mommy?
- Lily: Hmm?

990
01:09:55,677 --> 01:09:57,907
Katie:
Why is the Bible purple?

991
01:09:57,946 --> 01:10:00,210
(chuckles)
I don't know why it's purple.

992
01:10:00,249 --> 01:10:03,707
It was a wedding present.

993
01:10:03,752 --> 01:10:06,243
My grandmother brought it
all the way from Hungary.

994
01:10:06,288 --> 01:10:07,915
Someday it'll be yours.

995
01:10:11,560 --> 01:10:14,256
Are there people
where I'm going?

996
01:10:18,267 --> 01:10:22,431
Hey, you're not
going anywhere, kiddo.

997
01:10:22,471 --> 01:10:24,063
You're gonna stay
right here with us.

998
01:10:24,106 --> 01:10:26,131
Daddy...

999
01:10:26,175 --> 01:10:28,473
everyone dies.

1000
01:10:30,078 --> 01:10:32,410
When they're old.

1001
01:10:32,448 --> 01:10:34,040
When they're much older.

1002
01:10:34,082 --> 01:10:36,346
Okay, and then they go
to a better place.

1003
01:10:36,385 --> 01:10:39,377
And it's beautiful there.

1004
01:10:40,522 --> 01:10:42,353
And all your friends
will be there.

1005
01:10:48,163 --> 01:10:49,892
Is God there?

1006
01:10:50,933 --> 01:10:52,059
Yes.

1007
01:10:53,702 --> 01:10:55,567
Do you really
believe that, Daddy?

1008
01:10:57,139 --> 01:10:58,902
Yes.

1009
01:11:01,410 --> 01:11:03,401
Mike: You know what I think!
We should have done more!

1010
01:11:03,445 --> 01:11:05,106
- We did everything we could!
- No, we didn't!

1011
01:11:05,147 --> 01:11:07,411
- We should have helped her fight...
- Oh my God.

1012
01:11:07,449 --> 01:11:09,679
...instead of filling her head full
of these stories

1013
01:11:09,718 --> 01:11:11,982
about heavens
and the clouds and nirvana

1014
01:11:12,020 --> 01:11:13,851
and all that bullshit!

1015
01:11:13,889 --> 01:11:15,413
Those stories,
she like them.

1016
01:11:15,457 --> 01:11:17,288
I'm going to get
some cigarettes, okay?

1017
01:11:17,326 --> 01:11:19,089
(phone ringing)

1018
01:12:55,023 --> 01:12:58,151
