01:33:31,392 --> 01:33:34,259
(sobbing)

1270
01:33:37,231 --> 01:33:38,926
No.
No.

1271
01:33:38,966 --> 01:33:41,901
No. No.

1272
01:33:41,936 --> 01:33:43,870
You can't take her twice.

1273
01:33:45,806 --> 01:33:47,467
You can't.

1274
01:33:48,909 --> 01:33:51,878
Not again.
Please, God.

1275
01:33:51,912 --> 01:33:55,075
You can't.

1276
01:33:56,317 --> 01:33:58,342
Please.

1277
01:33:58,385 --> 01:34:00,353
No!

1278
01:34:00,387 --> 01:34:02,218
No.

1279
01:34:02,256 --> 01:34:05,248
- You bastard.
- # We fly #

1280
01:34:07,728 --> 01:34:12,859
# So many roads
to choose #

1281
01:34:12,900 --> 01:34:18,463
# We start out walking
and learn to run #

1282
01:34:18,505 --> 01:34:20,700
# And yet
we've just begun... #

1283
01:34:30,050 --> 01:34:31,483
(groans)

1284
01:34:31,518 --> 01:34:33,110
You little...

1285
01:34:33,153 --> 01:34:34,677
where is it?

1286
01:34:34,722 --> 01:34:36,952
Where?!
Where?!

1287
01:35:05,219 --> 01:35:10,486
(distorted) # We'll find a place
where there's room to grow #

1288
01:35:10,524 --> 01:35:14,927
# And yes,
we've just begun #

1289
01:35:18,165 --> 01:35:21,965
# Sharing horizons
that are new to us #

1290
01:35:23,671 --> 01:35:28,631
# Watching the signs
along the way #

1291
01:35:28,676 --> 01:35:31,873
# Talking it over,
just the two of us. #

1292
01:35:31,912 --> 01:35:32,446
(music stops)

1293
01:35:32,446 --> 01:35:33,606
(music stops)

1294
01:35:38,552 --> 01:35:40,952
(clock clicking)

1295
01:35:49,663 --> 01:35:52,291
(phone ringing)

1296
01:36:22,730 --> 01:36:24,561
Why don't you
just kill me?

1297
01:36:24,598 --> 01:36:26,463
Woman:
Because all guests of this hotel

1298
01:36:26,500 --> 01:36:28,297
enjoy free will,
Mr. Enslin.

1299
01:36:28,335 --> 01:36:31,031
You can choose to relive this hour
over and over,

1300
01:36:31,071 --> 01:36:34,336
or you can take advantage
of our express checkout system.

1301
01:37:05,506 --> 01:37:07,667
Mr. Enslin?

1302
01:37:19,053 --> 01:37:20,611
(wind howling)

1303
01:37:26,293 --> 01:37:28,056
(rumbling)

1304
01:37:34,234 --> 01:37:37,203
(flies buzzing)

1305
01:37:38,238 --> 01:37:40,433
(screams)

1306
01:37:51,218 --> 01:37:53,709
Are you ready to check out,
Mr. Enslin?

1307
01:37:56,857 --> 01:37:58,950
No.

1308
01:37:58,992 --> 01:38:01,153
- Not your way.
- I understand.

1309
01:38:02,930 --> 01:38:04,488
(rings)

1310
01:38:07,000 --> 01:38:09,298
By the way, Mr. Enslin,
your wife just called.

1311
01:38:09,336 --> 01:38:11,964
She'll be here in five minutes
and we'll send her straight up.

1312
01:38:12,005 --> 01:38:14,337
She's not involved.

1313
01:38:14,374 --> 01:38:17,207
You can't have her.

1314
01:38:17,244 --> 01:38:20,042
I'm done arguing with you.

1315
01:38:22,850 --> 01:38:24,613
I'm gonna end this.

1316
01:38:24,651 --> 01:38:26,676
Five.
This is five.

1317
01:38:26,720 --> 01:38:29,712
(voice distorts) Ignore the siren.
Even if you leave this room,

1318
01:38:29,756 --> 01:38:32,190
you can never
leave this room.

1319
01:38:32,226 --> 01:38:36,094
Eight.
This is eight.

1320
01:38:36,130 --> 01:38:39,395
We have killed
your friends.

1321
01:38:39,433 --> 01:38:41,958
Every friend

1322
01:38:42,002 --> 01:38:44,664
is now dead.

1323
01:38:54,848 --> 01:38:58,340
Mike's voice:
I lived the life of a selfish man.

1324
01:38:58,385 --> 01:39:01,786
But I don't have
to die that way.

1325
01:39:03,357 --> 01:39:04,756
If I'm going down,

1326
01:39:04,791 --> 01:39:07,954
I'm taking you with me.

1327
01:39:11,131 --> 01:39:13,099
This may not all be real,

1328
01:39:13,133 --> 01:39:15,795
and I may not even be real,

1329
01:39:15,836 --> 01:39:18,134
but this fire...

1330
01:39:21,041 --> 01:39:23,373
that's got to be real.

1331
01:39:33,554 --> 01:39:35,317
Go to hell!

1332
01:39:37,991 --> 01:39:39,856
(fire alarm ringing)

1333
01:39:53,774 --> 01:39:55,833
(clamoring)

1334
01:39:57,678 --> 01:39:59,145
Get out onto the street!

1335
01:39:59,179 --> 01:40:01,204
Out the doors
and onto the street, please.

1336
01:40:01,248 --> 01:40:03,648
Everyone stay calm.

1337
01:40:03,684 --> 01:40:06,847
- (honking)
- (sirens wailing)

1338
01:40:06,887 --> 01:40:09,981
- What's going on?
- Driver: I don't know, lady.

1339
01:40:10,023 --> 01:40:13,254
This might take a while.
Something must have happened.

1340
01:40:13,293 --> 01:40:15,659
Thanks.

1341
01:40:15,696 --> 01:40:18,062
(distorted music playing)

1342
01:40:21,368 --> 01:40:23,393
(man moaning)

1343
01:40:23,437 --> 01:40:26,736
Keep quiet,
you bastard.

1344
01:40:28,542 --> 01:40:30,373
Please, you've gotta help me.
No, help me.

1345
01:40:30,410 --> 01:40:31,775
- Calm down.
- My husband's inside.

1346
01:40:31,812 --> 01:40:33,871
My husband's inside.
You've gotta help him.

1347
01:40:33,914 --> 01:40:35,677
You've gotta help him,
please!

1348
01:40:35,716 --> 01:40:37,115
What floor?
What floor?

1349
01:40:37,150 --> 01:40:39,277
14th floor, 1408.
Mike Enslin.

1350
01:40:39,319 --> 01:40:41,753
Please come here.

1351
01:40:41,788 --> 01:40:45,588
- (moaning)
- You're wasting your time.

1352
01:40:51,098 --> 01:40:53,692
We're here
to do the job,

1353
01:40:53,734 --> 01:40:55,861
and we don't rattle.

1354
01:40:59,306 --> 01:41:02,036
The decor is in tatters

1355
01:41:02,075 --> 01:41:03,975
and the staff surly.

1356
01:41:04,011 --> 01:41:06,946
But on the Shiver Scale...

1357
01:41:08,348 --> 01:41:11,613
I award the Dolphin
10 skulls!

1358
01:41:22,262 --> 01:41:24,457
(crowd screaming)

1359
01:41:33,106 --> 01:41:35,438
(coughing)

1360
01:41:35,475 --> 01:41:38,342
Never kill
more than you can eat.

1361
01:41:45,285 --> 01:41:47,185
(chuckling)

1362
01:41:47,220 --> 01:41:50,348
Katie:
Daddy, everyone dies.

1363
01:41:50,390 --> 01:41:52,517
(laughing)

1364
01:42:21,054 --> 01:42:24,285
We commend to Almighty God
our brother,

1365
01:42:24,324 --> 01:42:27,384
and we commit his body
to the ground,

1366
01:42:27,427 --> 01:42:30,988
earth to earth,
ashes to ashes,

1367
01:42:31,031 --> 01:42:34,592
dust to dust.

1368
01:42:34,634 --> 01:42:36,295
May you rest in peace.

1369
01:42:36,336 --> 01:42:38,133
Amen.

1370
01:42:38,171 --> 01:42:39,900
All: Amen.

1371
01:42:39,940 --> 01:42:42,408
Well, they're together now.

1372
01:42:46,580 --> 01:42:48,844
Let's go.

1373
01:42:56,289 --> 01:42:58,484
Olin:
Mrs. Enslin?

1374
01:43:02,829 --> 01:43:05,320
I...

1375
01:43:05,365 --> 01:43:07,731
I am sorry to intrude at such
a delicate time,

1376
01:43:07,768 --> 01:43:10,566
but I knew your husband.
I worked at the Dolphin.

1377
01:43:10,604 --> 01:43:12,572
Oh.

1378
01:43:12,606 --> 01:43:15,473
While we were cleaning up,
we came across some of his belongings.

1379
01:43:15,509 --> 01:43:17,875
No, thank you.

1380
01:43:17,911 --> 01:43:19,902
They are of such
a personal nature, ma'am.

1381
01:43:19,946 --> 01:43:22,073
- I figured maybe you would want to...
- No, please.

1382
01:43:22,115 --> 01:43:24,310
It's not how
I want to remember him.

1383
01:43:24,351 --> 01:43:26,751
I'm sure you understand.

1384
01:43:26,787 --> 01:43:28,448
Oh yes, yes.
Of course I understand.

1385
01:43:28,488 --> 01:43:31,150
But it's important that you know
that he did a great thing.

1386
01:43:31,191 --> 01:43:33,386
He did not die
in vain.

1387
01:43:33,427 --> 01:43:35,725
What are you talking about?

1388
01:43:35,762 --> 01:43:37,923
Because of him,
the room won't reopen. It's been...

1389
01:43:37,964 --> 01:43:40,057
All right, okay, stop.

1390
01:43:40,100 --> 01:43:42,933
Just give
the lady some air.

1391
01:43:42,969 --> 01:43:45,199
She's been through enough,
don't you think?

1392
01:44:26,012 --> 01:44:29,914
(static)

1393
01:44:29,950 --> 01:44:31,975
Mike:
Round one goes to the hideous Mr. Olin

1394
01:44:32,018 --> 01:44:33,315
for effective
aggressiveness.

1395
01:44:33,353 --> 01:44:35,787
I have to admit,
he had me going.

1396
01:44:35,822 --> 01:44:37,255
Get ahold of yourself.

1397
01:44:37,290 --> 01:44:39,952
You're running to places
that aren't real.

1398
01:44:39,993 --> 01:44:41,517
Katie:
Daddy,

1399
01:44:41,561 --> 01:44:43,552
don't you
love me anymore?

1400
01:44:43,597 --> 01:44:45,724
Mike:
Of course I do, sweetheart.

1401
01:44:45,765 --> 01:44:48,325
- Don't you love me, Daddy?
- Of course I do, honey,

1402
01:44:48,368 --> 01:44:50,563
more than anything.
I got you now.

1403
01:44:50,604 --> 01:44:53,232
I got you right here, sweetie.
Everything's fine.

1404
01:44:53,273 --> 01:44:56,640
I got you, Katie.
Nobody's ever gonna take you away again.

1405
01:44:56,676 --> 01:44:58,473
Katie:
Daddy?

1406
01:44:58,512 --> 01:45:01,572
Daddy!
Daddy!

1407
01:45:01,615 --> 01:45:03,674
Daddy!

1408
01:45:03,717 --> 01:45:06,049
Daddy!

1409
01:45:10,223 --> 01:45:11,850
(screams)

1410
01:45:14,494 --> 01:45:16,052
Hey, sweetie.

1411
01:45:55,201 --> 01:45:57,863
(siren wailing)

1412
01:46:07,547 --> 01:46:10,072
(wind howling)

1413
01:46:16,556 --> 01:46:18,717
Katie:
Daddy!

1414
01:46:18,758 --> 01:46:21,750
Daddy!

1415
01:46:21,795 --> 01:46:24,263
Yes, of course.

1416
01:46:29,135 --> 01:46:31,262
(door slams)

1417
01:46:34,708 --> 01:46:36,938
(instrumental music playing)

